      "span_text": "Of these healed patients, 94% remained fully healed after 9-12 months of follow-up  compared to the standard of care that only healed 0 and 8%, respectively.  The goal of this study was to elucidate an important aspect of the mechanism of action of dHACM for accelerating chronic wound healing, as observed clinically in diabetic patients, by demonstrating the impact of dHACM on diabetic stem cell proliferation, migration, and gene expression."
